From: Al Viro <viro@zeniv.linux.org.uk>
Date: Wed, 4 Jun 2025 12:27:08 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] do_change_type(): refuse to operate on unmounted/not ours
 mounts
Git-commit: 12f147ddd6de7382dad54812e65f3f08d05809fc
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: CVE-2025-38498 bsc#1247374

Ensure that propagation settings can only be changed for mounts located
in the caller's mount namespace. This change aligns permission checking
with the rest of mount(2).

Reviewed-by: Christian Brauner <brauner@kernel.org>
Fixes: 07b20889e305 ("beginning of the shared-subtree proper")
Reported-by: "Orlando, Noah" <Noah.Orlando@deshaw.com>
Signed-off-by: Al Viro <viro@zeniv.linux.org.uk>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 fs/namespace.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/fs/namespace.c
+++ b/fs/namespace.c
@@ -2371,6 +2371,10 @@ static int do_change_type(struct path *p
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	namespace_lock();
+	if (!check_mnt(mnt)) {
+		err = -EINVAL;
+		goto out_unlock;
+	}
 	if (type == MS_SHARED) {
 		err = invent_group_ids(mnt, recurse);
 		if (err)
